{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":750,"text":"I'm a very lucky person."},{"time":4059,"text":"I've been privileged to see so much of our beautiful Earth"},{"time":8537,"text":"and the people and creatures that live on it."},{"time":10865,"text":"And my passion was inspired at the age of seven,"},{"time":14485,"text":"when my parents first took me to Morocco,"},{"time":16820,"text":"at the edge of the Sahara Desert."},{"time":18946,"text":"Now imagine a little Brit"},{"time":21321,"text":"somewhere that wasn't cold and damp like home."},{"time":24442,"text":"What an amazing experience."},{"time":26718,"text":"And it made me want to explore more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29211,"text":"So as a filmmaker,"},{"time":31814,"text":"I've been from one end of the Earth to the other"},{"time":34625,"text":"trying to get the perfect shot"},{"time":37333,"text":"and to capture animal behavior never seen before."},{"time":41125,"text":"And what's more, I'm really lucky,"},{"time":43757,"text":"because I get to share that with millions of people worldwide."},{"time":46875,"text":"Now the idea of having new perspectives of our planet"},{"time":52125,"text":"and actually being able to get that message out"},{"time":55958,"text":"gets me out of bed every day with a spring in my step."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58816,"text":"You might think that it's quite hard"},{"time":61958,"text":"to find new stories and new subjects,"},{"time":64208,"text":"but new technology is changing the way we can film."},{"time":68539,"text":"It's enabling us to get fresh, new images"},{"time":72375,"text":"and tell brand new stories."},{"time":74492,"text":"In Nature's Great Events,"},{"time":77375,"text":"a series for the BBC that I did with David Attenborough,"},{"time":80917,"text":"we wanted to do just that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83167,"text":"Images of grizzly bears are pretty familiar."},{"time":86208,"text":"You see them all the time, you think."},{"time":89458,"text":"But there's a whole side to their lives that we hardly ever see"},{"time":93542,"text":"and had never been filmed."},{"time":95250,"text":"So what we did, we went to Alaska,"},{"time":99500,"text":"which is where the grizzlies rely"},{"time":101868,"text":"on really high, almost inaccessible, mountain slopes"},{"time":104854,"text":"for their denning."},{"time":106789,"text":"And the only way to film that is a shoot from the air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114304,"text":"(Video) David Attenborough: Throughout Alaska and British Columbia,"},{"time":118917,"text":"thousands of bear families are emerging from their winter sleep."},{"time":124129,"text":"There is nothing to eat up here,"},{"time":128083,"text":"but the conditions were ideal for hibernation."},{"time":131583,"text":"Lots of snow in which to dig a den."},{"time":139450,"text":"To find food, mothers must lead their cubs down to the coast,"},{"time":145440,"text":"where the snow will already be melting."},{"time":152502,"text":"But getting down can be a challenge for small cubs."},{"time":185723,"text":"These mountains are dangerous places,"},{"time":189458,"text":"but ultimately the fate of these bear families,"},{"time":192917,"text":"and indeed that of all bears around the North Pacific,"},{"time":196431,"text":"depends on the salmon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201064,"text":"KB: I love that shot."},{"time":203625,"text":"I always get goosebumps every time I see it."},{"time":205917,"text":"That was filmed from a helicopter"},{"time":207958,"text":"using a gyro-stabilized camera."},{"time":210750,"text":"And it's a wonderful bit of gear,"},{"time":213208,"text":"because it's like having a flying tripod, crane and dolly all rolled into one."},{"time":217167,"text":"But technology alone isn't enough."},{"time":220375,"text":"To really get the money shots,"},{"time":222875,"text":"it's down to being in the right place at the right time."},{"time":225917,"text":"And that sequence was especially difficult."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228875,"text":"The first year we got nothing."},{"time":232375,"text":"We had to go back the following year,"},{"time":235958,"text":"all the way back to the remote parts of Alaska."},{"time":238958,"text":"And we hung around with a helicopter for two whole weeks."},{"time":241583,"text":"And eventually we got lucky."},{"time":244625,"text":"The cloud lifted, the wind was still,"},{"time":248958,"text":"and even the bear showed up."},{"time":250708,"text":"And we managed to get that magic moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253292,"text":"For a filmmaker,"},{"time":255167,"text":"new technology is an amazing tool,"},{"time":259340,"text":"but the other thing that really, really excites me"},{"time":262546,"text":"is when new species are discovered."},{"time":265500,"text":"Now, when I heard about one animal,"},{"time":267787,"text":"I knew we had to get it for my next series,"},{"time":270750,"text":"Untamed Americas, for National Geographic."},{"time":273500,"text":"In 2005, a new species of bat was discovered"},{"time":279811,"text":"in the cloud forests of Ecuador."},{"time":282083,"text":"And what was amazing about that discovery"},{"time":284167,"text":"is that it also solved the mystery"},{"time":286583,"text":"of what pollinated a unique flower."},{"time":289620,"text":"It depends solely on the bat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291583,"text":"Now, the series hasn't even aired yet,"},{"time":294317,"text":"so you're the very first to see this."},{"time":296744,"text":"See what you think."},{"time":301590,"text":"(Video) Narrator: The tube-lipped nectar bat."},{"time":310536,"text":"A pool of delicious nectar"},{"time":312877,"text":"lies at the bottom of each flower's long flute."},{"time":315042,"text":"But how to reach it?"},{"time":319887,"text":"Necessity is the mother of evolution."},{"time":325083,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":348489,"text":"This two-and-a-half-inch bat"},{"time":351496,"text":"has a three-and-a-half-inch tongue,"},{"time":358221,"text":"the longest relative to body length"},{"time":362119,"text":"of any mammal in the world."},{"time":364438,"text":"If human, he'd have a nine-foot tongue."},{"time":376122,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":378612,"text":"KB: What a tongue."},{"time":380677,"text":"We filmed it by cutting a tiny little hole in the base of the flower"},{"time":385542,"text":"and using a camera that could slow the action by 40 times."},{"time":390167,"text":"So imagine how quick that thing is in real life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393250,"text":"Now people often ask me, \"Where's your favorite place on the planet?\""},{"time":398462,"text":"And the truth is I just don't have one."},{"time":400995,"text":"There are so many wonderful places."},{"time":403542,"text":"But some locations draw you back time and time again."},{"time":407042,"text":"And one remote location --"},{"time":409790,"text":"I first went there as a backpacker;"},{"time":411810,"text":"I've been back several times for filming,"},{"time":414125,"text":"most recently for Untamed Americas --"},{"time":415875,"text":"it's the Altiplano in the high Andes of South America,"},{"time":420625,"text":"and it's the most otherworldly place I know."},{"time":425792,"text":"But at 15,000 feet, it's tough."},{"time":428894,"text":"It's freezing cold,"},{"time":430417,"text":"and that thin air really gets you."},{"time":435083,"text":"Sometimes it's hard to breathe,"},{"time":437394,"text":"especially carrying all the heavy filming equipment."},{"time":440437,"text":"And that pounding head just feels like a constant hangover."},{"time":445042,"text":"But the advantage of that wonderful thin atmosphere"},{"time":449333,"text":"is that it enables you to see the stars in the heavens"},{"time":453271,"text":"with amazing clarity."},{"time":455710,"text":"Have a look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459896,"text":"(Video) Narrator: Some 1,500 miles south of the tropics,"},{"time":463552,"text":"between Chile and Bolivia,"},{"time":465237,"text":"the Andes completely change."},{"time":470413,"text":"It's called the Altiplano, or \"high plains\" --"},{"time":475042,"text":"a place of extremes"},{"time":478925,"text":"and extreme contrasts."},{"time":482614,"text":"Where deserts freeze"},{"time":487125,"text":"and waters boil."},{"time":490958,"text":"More like Mars than Earth,"},{"time":494458,"text":"it seems just as hostile to life."},{"time":505196,"text":"The stars themselves --"},{"time":515065,"text":"at 12,000 feet, the dry, thin air"},{"time":518786,"text":"makes for perfect stargazing."},{"time":526929,"text":"Some of the world's astronomers have telescopes nearby."},{"time":532813,"text":"But just looking up with the naked eye,"},{"time":536885,"text":"you really don't need one."},{"time":540130,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":587140,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":593167,"text":"KB: Thank you so much"},{"time":596484,"text":"for letting me share some images"},{"time":598958,"text":"of our magnificent, wonderful Earth."},{"time":601867,"text":"Thank you for letting me share that with you."},{"time":603764,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}